                  Shift4 Payments, LLC
 Conflicts of Interest Disclosure and Certification

I. 	Purpose

      The purpose of this Conflicts of Interest Disclosure and Certification (this "Disclosure") is to:
     (i)    	detail certain relationships and/or activities that may create an
            actual or perceived conflict of interest for employees and officers
            of Shift4 Payments, LLC and its subsidiaries (collectively, the
            "Company");
     (ii)   	set forth the Company's expectations regarding how to address
            such Conflicts of Interest (as defined below); and
     (iii)  	obtain certifications as to such individual's compliance with the
            above.
II. Disclosure

      The Company expects that all personnel will conduct the Company's business
with the highest level of integrity. 	This means, among other things, avoiding
conflicts between personal interests and the interests of the Company. 	A "Conflict
of Interest" exists when a person's private interest interferes in any way - 	or
even appears to interfere - 	with the interests of the Company. 	A conflict
situation can arise when an employee or 	officer, or a member of his or her
family, takes actions or has interests that may make it difficult to perform
his or her Company work objectively and effectively. Conflicts of interest also
arise when an employee or 	officer, or a member of his or her family, receives
improper personal benefits as 	a result of his or her position in the Company.
Loans to, or guarantees of obligations of, employees and officers and their
family members may create conflicts of interest.

    It 	is 	almost always a conflict of interest for a Company employee or officer to
work for, make a substantive investment in, or serve on the board of directors of
a competitor, customer or supplier of the Company.
    All such Conflicts of Interest are prohibited unless specifically acknowledged
and waived in 	writing by the Company's General Counsel or his or her designee.

   	Each 	employee and officer must disclose the Conflicts of Interest listed
below of which they are 	aware, whether on their own behalf or on behalf of a member
of their immediate family (spouse, parents, 	children, and siblings, as 	well as
in-laws and those with whom they share 	a 	household), if such interests could
be 	construed as being 	a 	Conflict of Interest with the Company.
